7 Section 2. Section 27-1-741, MCA, is amended to read:
8 "27-1-741. Purpose. The legislature finds that:
9 (1) amusement rides are used by a large number of Montana's citizens and attract a large number
10 of nonresidents, significantly contributing to Montana's tourism industry and tax base;
11 (2) the safety of the public using amusement rides is an important matter of public policy;
12 (3) there are inherent risks associated with the machinery, equipment, or animals that are
13 impracticable or impossible for an amusement ride owner or operator to eliminate with all reasonable safety
14 precautions;
15 (4) an informed patron is in the best position to avoid risks inherent to amusement rides; and
16 (5) the safety of amusement rides will be greatly improved at minimal cost if operators maintain
17 minimum safety standards and riders are subject to minimum safety standards for their own protection and the
18 protection of others."
19
